omba Gira’s role in the rivalries, relationships, and struggles of everyday life in urban Brazil.A DVD of the film Slaves of the Saints is included.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAfro-Brazilian cultszBrazil. 0aPomba-Gira. 0aPombagira (Afro-Brazilian deity). 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh  aafro brazilian.  aanthropology.  ablack magic.  abrazil.  acontemporary brazil.  acontroversial figures.  afemininity.  afeminism.  agender politics.  agender studies.  agendered violence.  amagic.  amodern history.  amorality.  amystical.  anonfiction.  apomba gira.  aprostitution.  areligious figures.  areligious practices.  ario de janeiro.  arituals.  asex politics.  asexuality.  asocial marginality.  asocial science.  aspirits.  aspirituality.  asuperstitious.  aurban brazil.  aworld religions.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052026265240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094943040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520949430423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520949430/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY